Class ParsingResult<V>

java.lang.Object
  org.parboiled.support.ParsingResult<V>

@WillBeFinal(version="1.1")
public class ParsingResult<V>
extends Object

A simple container encapsulating the result of a parsing run.

Method Detail

isSuccess

public final boolean isSuccess()
Return true if this parse result is a match

Note that a result NOT having a match does not mean that it has collected parse errors (see hasCollectedParseErrors(); a BasicParseRunner, for instance, does not collect errors.

Returns:
see description

getParseTree

@Nullable
public final Node<V> getParseTree()
Gets the generated parse tree, if any

Only a ReportingParseRunner will generate a parse tree.

Returns:
the tree, or (unfortunately) null if no tree

getTopStackValue

@Nullable
public final V getTopStackValue()
Gets the value at the top of the stack, if any

Note that unfortunately the top of the stack can also be null, so this method is not reliable.

hasCollectedParseErrors

public final boolean hasCollectedParseErrors()
Has this result collected any parse errors?

note: this method does not guarantee that the result is a success; for this use isSuccess() instead.

Returns:
true if the parse error list is not empty

hasErrors

@Deprecated
@Unused
public boolean hasErrors()
Deprecated. name is confusing; use isSuccess() to see if this result is a match and hasCollectedParseErrors() if this result has collected parse errors.

Returns:
true if this parsing result contains parsing errors.
